Solution Walkthrough for Riddle Registry
Step 1: Initial Analysis

First, I downloaded the PDF file and performed basic reconnaissance using exiftool, a powerful tool for extracting metadata from files:
bash

exiftool confidential.pdf

Step 2: Examining the Metadata

The exiftool output revealed important metadata about the PDF:
text

ExifTool Version Number         : 13.25
File Name                       : confidential.pdf
Directory                       : .
File Size                       : 183 kB
File Modification Date/Time     : 2026:02:21 18:09:59-05:00
File Access Date/Time           : 2026:02:21 18:11:30-05:00
File Inode Change Date/Time     : 2026:02:21 18:09:59-05:00
File Permissions                : -rw-rw-r--
File Type                       : PDF
File Type Extension             : pdf
MIME Type                       : application/pdf
PDF Version                     : 1.7
Linearized                      : No
Page Count                      : 1
Producer                        : PyPDF2
Author                          : cGljb0NURntwdXp6bDNkX20zdGFkYXRhX2YwdW5kIV8zNTc4NzM5YX0=

Step 3: Identifying the Hidden Data

The key finding was in the Author field, which contained what appeared to be a base64-encoded string:

cGljb0NURntwdXp6bDNkX20zdGFkYXRhX2YwdW5kIV8zNTc4NzM5YX0=

Base64 encoding is commonly used in CTF challenges to hide plaintext data. The string ended with an equals sign (=), which is a telltale padding character used in base64 encoding.
Step 4: Decoding the Base64 String

I decoded the string using the base64 command-line utility:

echo "cGljb0NURntwdXp6bDNkX20zdGFkYXRhX2YwdW5kIV8zNTc4NzM5YX0=" | base64 -d
